x4freetext: SIN CYCLOTRON, DELIVERING A 590 MEV PROTON BEAM
WITH 1 NS BEAM PULSES AT A REPETITION RATE OF 50.63
590 MEV PROTONS ONTO A 12 CM THICK BE-TARGET, O
.590 MEV PROTONS ONTO A 5.8 CM THICK AL2O3-TARGET. THE
NEUTRONS WERE PRODUCED AT AN ANGLE OF 60 MRAD. THE
GAMMA CONTAMINATION WAS REDUCED BY AN 8 CM THICK LEAD
FILTER. THE NEUTRON BEAM WAS COLLIMATED TO 1.2 CM BY
SENSITIVE MULTI-WIRE DRIFT CHAMBERS, WAS USED
TO DETECT RECOIL PROTONS FROM LIQUID HYDROGEN CON-
TAINED IN A CYLINDRICAL CELL OF 8 CM DIAMETER. THIS
SYSTEM HAD RESOLUTION ENOUGH TO DISCRIMINATE BETWEEN
TIME-OF-FLIGHT EVENTS FROM DIFFERENT BEAM-BURSTS. THE
NEUTRON DETECTION EQUIPMENT WAS PLACED AT A DISTANCE
OF 60 M FROM THE NEUTRON PRODUCTION TARGET. THE
NEUTRON ENERGY RESOLUTION WAS BETTER THAN 1.5 PERCENT
IN THE WHOLO ENERGY RANGE 150 - 600 MEV.
A CH2 SCATTERER IN THE BEAM AND A THREE-FOLD
SCINTILLATION TELESCOPE AT AN ANGLE OF 30 DEGREES
.NATURAL SAMPLES OF BE, C, AL, V, MN, CO, CU, AG, CE,
TA, PB, BI AND U, HAVING A CROSS SECTION AREA OF 5CM
BY 5 CM, WERE USED. A WATER SAMPLE WAS USED FOR THE
OXYGEN MEASUREMENTS. THE LENGTH OF THE ABSORPTION
SAMPLES VARIED FROM 3.3 CM FOR URANIUM TO 17 CM FOR
CARBON IN ORDER TO HAVE A TRANSMISSION OF ABOUT 0.6 AT
500 MEV. THE WATER SAMPLE HAD A LENGTH OF 37 CM. THE
ABSORBATION SAMPLES WERE PLACED AT A DISTANCE OF 25 M
